This is a simple demo program for doing genotyping, methylation calling and haplotyping.

Installation:
- check out the repository: git clone git@github.com:benedictpaten/marginPhase.git
- check out submodules: cd marginPhase ; git submodule update --init
- build htsLib (only required once): cd externalTools/htsLib ; autoconf ; autoheader ; ./configure ; make
- make build directory: mkdir build ; cd build
- generate Makefile with cmake: cmake ..
- build with make: make

- to run marginPhase: ./marginPhase -b ../examples/NA12878.pb.chr3.100kb.bam -p ../params.json

- to run tests: ./allTests
(this currently only runs the single newest marginPhase test. To run the ones from before, you can uncomment the line in main in allTests.c)


